article.headline: Bowling Green 69, Toledo 58
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Nate Miller scored 21 points and had 11 rebounds as Bowling Green rolled past Toledo, 69-58, on Sunday. Bowling Green (11-11, 6-4 Mid-American) led 35-23 at halftime, and increased their margin to 15 points early in the second half. The Falcons held on as Toledo (7-15, 4-6) could shoot just 32.4 percent in the final period. Darryl Clements and Otis Polk each scored 12 points and Chris Knight grabbed 10 rebounds for Bowling Green. Tyrone Kent scored 15 points and Jerrah Young had 14 for Toledo. Bowling Green outrebounded Toledo 39-24 and shot 54.2 percent to the Rockets' 35.2 percent for the game.
